==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in the 1300s, a variant of ''[[abominable]]'', possibly influenced by {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|ab}} + {{m|la|homine||man}}.<ref>{{R:MW3 1976|page=3}}</ref> The unnecessary addition of ''h'' to words was once common; compare ''abholish'' (''abolish''). Abandoned by the 1600s.<ref>{{R:CDOE|page=4}}</ref>. Compare also {{m|en|abhomination}}.

